review_blob: Pours a pale caramel color with a little bit of white head.  Aroma is very mild...almost non-existent, but maybe a hint of malt.  Strong carbonation with a thin mouthfeel.  Flavor is moderately sweet with hint of caramel and malt.  Not very hoppy.  Clean finish.   Not much to this, but its drinkable.
beer_name: Widmer Brothers Drop Top Amber Ale

review_blob:
They have this beer on tap in Heaven.
This tops my former favorite beer, New Belgium 1554.  Yes, it looks like motor oil, but it tastes like paradise.  Very heavy.  Almost syrupy mouthfeel...but if you know that going in, it doesnt matter.  Alcohol kicks you in the head after about three sips.  Maybe thats why my review is glowing so brightly!

Pours a dark reddish brown with a lot of tan head.  Aroma is hoppy with an alcohol bite.  Flavor is mild, with a bit of coffee and caramel and a slightly hoppy aftertaste.  Thin mouthfeel and a tad watery, but better as its temperature rose in the glass. Not bad.
beer_name: Big Sky Moose Drool Brown Ale

review_blob: Pours a darkish red amber with a tan head.  Not much aroma.  Flavor is smokey with a bit of coffee and malt.  Hoppy aftertaste.  Not bad.  Retired, but Id be willing to bet it will be back.

Pours a reddish, dark-brown, cola color with a fair amount of light tan head.  Aroma is mild, a little malty and lemony.  Flavor is bright and citrus with a  sweet maltiness and a hint of chocolate and smoke.  I love this beer.  The low ratings surprise me, but Voodoo strays from the Schwarzbier standard and is probably not a favorite of most hopheads.  Oh well...more for me!

Pours a hazy honey color with a nice amount of yellowish head.  Earthy aroma of malt and bananas with a lot of spice.  Flavor is very sweet--fruity, with coriander and some clove.  A slightly bitter aftertaste.  Pretty good.

Pours a golden color with a lot of white, bubbly head.  Aroma is sweet and soapy with a hint of clove.  Flavor is bittersweet with a bit of hops, some citrus and more clove.  Soft mouthfeel with mild carbonation.  Very good.

Pours a nice amber-red with a good amount of tan head.  Aroma is reminiscent of black olives with a bit of alcohol bite.  Flavor is sweet and smokey with a hint of hops  A little watery, but otherwise quite good.
Pours a caramel color with a large tan head.  Mild aroma; a bit of hops and alcohol.  Flavor is very hoppy with some bitter coffee and charcoal.  Medium body and carbonation.

Pours a clear golden yellow with nice amount of almost white head.  Aroma is sweet and malty with a hint of banana.  Flavor is sweet and just a little spicy.  Some earthiness in the finish but overall a bit watery.  Not bad.

Pours a hazy honey color with a nice amount of white head.  Aroma is sweet bananas and a lot of malt.  Flavor is sweet, nutty and fruity.  A bit of hops in the background and an alcohol bite at the finish.  Nicely carbonated.  One of my favorites.

Pours a dark amber with a small amount of tan head which diminishes quickly.  Malty aroma with an alcohol bite.  Flavor is hoppy and semisweet.  Thick mouth feel.  Fruity, mildly bitter aftertaste.  Great stuff.

Pours a very dark brown with a small amount of tan head.  Mild aroma of hops and charcoal.  Flavor is bitter, with a lot of dark chocolate and charcoal  A little sweetness in the aftertaste.  Not bad.

beer_brewer_name: Portland Brewing Company (Pyramid - North American Breweries)
review_blob: Dark amber color with a foamy tan head.  Bold, hoppy aroma.  Flavor is malty with a bit of soapy sourness.  Sweet, nutty aftertaste.  Nice mouth feel.  Good stuff.
Pours a reddish-brown with a small amount of white head. Not much aroma. Flavor is mild. A little hops, some clove, nicely sweet. Nothing special, but very drinkable.
Pours a hazy golden color with a lot of bright white head. Mild aroma, though a bit skunky. Bittersweet flavor with a lot of spice; coriander, clove, hint of apricot. Yeasty good stuff.
Pours a dark golden with a small amount of white head. Aroma is hoppy and mild. Flavor is the same, with just enough grapefruit bitterness and a touch of honey sweetness. This is a pale ale I like.

Bottle at the Flying Saucer in San Antonio. Pours a deep, dark brown with a lot of creamy tan head. Light coffee or mocha aroma. Flavor is roasted coffee beans with a vinegary bitterness at the end. Watery, thin mouthfeel. Interesting but not great.

On tap at the Flying Saucer in San Antonio. Pours a pale yellow with lots of haze and a creamy white head. Not much aroma. Flavor is mildly sweet with a little hops and lots of malt and wheat. Citrus, clove, nicely spiced. Great beer.
Pours a golden-yellow with a lot of bright white head. Nice, sweet, malty aroma. Flavor is very malty with a little hoppy bitterness. Quite a bit of sediment. Thin mouthfeel, but overall pretty good.
Pours a hazy golden-yellow with quite a bit of sediment. Mild aroma of yeast and citrus. Watery flavor, with a bit sweet grain and breadiness. OK, but not great.
Dirty yellow with some sediment and a little white head. Aroma is earthy and malty. Flavor is mildly sweet with some coriander, banana and a peppery finish. Nicely carbonated. Good stuff.
A dark cola color with a lot of creamy-tan head.  Mildly hoppy aroma.  Lightly flavored and a bit thin.  A little charcoal bitterness and some sweet malt.  Nothing special.
Brownish copper color with very little head.  Sharp, hoppy aroma.  Sweet with a hint of smokiness and hops.  A bit thin and watery.  Well carbonated.  Pretty good, but not great.
Dirty yellow color with big bubbles and little to no head.  Almost no aroma.  Lots of carbonation.  Taste is a little hoppy and bitter.  Not all that great, but marginally better than regular Bud.

Honey colored with a surprising amount of sediment.  Hoppy aroma, but a bit skunky.  Flavor is light.  A lot of hoppy bitterness, but not overpowering.  A bit of orange peel and some metallic aftertaste.  Good stuff.
A light copper color with lots of sediment.  Head is a frothy tan.  Not much aroma.  Flavor is a bit too sweet.  Hoppy, but not bitter, with a hint of straw and nuttiness.  Not all that great.

Sold in a 25 ounce "corked" bottle.  Pours a cloudy yellow with a long-lasting white head.  Mild wheat aroma.  Flavor has a strong alcohol bite with a bit of citrus, lemon, and clove.  Good stuff, especially after the 8.5% alcohol kicks in!
Pours a dark golden color.  Nice, fine head that dissipates quickly.  Malty aroma.  Flavor is malt with some hops and mild charcoal.  A hint of citrus.  Not bad.

Pours a golden-orange color.  A little bit of white head that disappears quickly.  Aroma is cinnamon, cloves, and pumpkin.  Strong pumpkin flavor, with a little sweet hoppiness and lots of cloves.  Not bad for a gimmicky brew.
Pours dark brown with a thick, long-lasting tan head.  Not much aroma.  Bittersweet, coffee,  hops.  Tangy aftertaste with a little charcoal.  Thin consistency, but bold flavor.  Not bad.

Dirty tan color with a thick off-white head.  Mild malty aroma.  Interesting flavor...  Flowery?  Lilac maybe?  Some citrus, too.  Yes, honey as well, but not too sweet.  I actually liked this a lot.  But it looks like Im the only one!

Pours black with a big, creamy-brown head.  Aroma is nice, with a chocolaty, alcohol bite.  Flavor is bittersweet, with hints of chocolate, coffee, and blackberry.  Good carbonation, but just a bit thin.  Great beer.

Pale golden color with a small amount of white head.  Malty, grainy aroma.  Fruity flavor with hints of peach and apricot.  Lots of malty flavor.  A bit watery.  I thought this was pretty good stuff, but it seems under rated here.  Then again, I like Rolling Rock...

Dirty straw color with a nice amount of sediment.  Bright white head.  Strong wheat aroma.  Nice flavor.  Lots of coriander and clove but not too sweet.  A bit of banana and hops.  Good carbonation.  A bit of a sour aftertaste.  Good beer.
Dark coppery color with a LOT of tan head.  Sharp, hoppy aroma.  Flavor is hops and metal with a bit of charcoal and soap.  Not much carbonation...probably all came out in the pour.   Not bad.
Cloudy orange color with a lot of bright white head.  Nice malty aroma.  Flavor is hoppy with a strong grapefruit twang, a little sweetness, and a metallic aftertaste.  Not bad.
Pours a deep copper color with a small amount of white head.  Mild, hoppy aroma.  Nice flavor, with moderate hops, a little caramel, and a bit of metallic aftertaste.  Not bad.
Nice amber color with a lot of whitish head.  Lemony, metallic aroma.  Hoppy flavor with a lingering charcoal and metal aftertaste.  A bit thin, but OK.
Pours an amber orange with a fair amount of tan head.  Pleasant malty aroma.  Flavor is sweet, with some fruitiness and mild smokiness.  Lingering aftertaste and a little watery.  Not bad.

Pours a watery dark brown with big bubbles.  Looks just like a cola in the glass.  Nice malty, earthy aroma.  Good flavor.  Lots of chocolate, coffee, and some sweetness.  A hint of fruit...prunes?!  Thin mouthfeel for a beer this dark, but overall a good brew.
Pours a golden yellow with a bright white head.  Mild, soapy aroma.  Flavor is crisp, metallic, with some citrus (orange) notes and a hint of apricot.  Somewhat watery.  Not bad.

Pours a pale orange with a fair amount of white head.  Aroma is hoppy.  Flavor is bold, strongly metallic, with lots of grapefruit bitterness.  Lingering aftertaste and a moderately heavy mouthfeel.  A good IPA, but Im not much of a fan of IPAs...

Pours a straw color with a bright white head.  Very mild aroma, but with a hint of something unpleasant...swampy?  Flavor is better.  A hint of citrus, hops, and old yeast.  Earthy aftertaste.  Not great, but drinkable.
Pours a dirty yellow color with lots of cloudiness and quite a bit of white head.  Aroma is malty.  Flavor is bitter, with a hint of malt and some citrus.  Nothing special about this one.
Pours a bright orange-amber color with a fair amount of white head.  Bold, hoppy aroma.  Flavor is also nice and hoppy with a bit of grapefruit and charcoal.  Somewhat watery and thin mouthfeel.  OK.

Pours a medium orange-amber with a good amount of whitish head.  Aroma is mild and hoppy.  Flavor is a bit bland for an IPA.  A little metal, a few notes of grapefruit, some lingering hoppy aftertaste.  OK, though probably not bold enough for a true IPA fan.
Light amber color with a little bit of white head.  Mild hoppy aroma.  Lots of carbonation.  Very mild flavor.  Malty and somewhat sweet with a hint charcoal.  OK.
UPDATED: FEB 17, 2008
On tap in Louisville.  Pours black with no head.  Mild aroma.  Strong alcohol taste--like a shot of bourbon!  Coffee and smokey overtones.  Light mouthful for a stout.  Good stuff.
